{
  "texts": [
    "We also compared all amino acid-level models, as shown in Fig. 4.",
    "We observed that the predictions from the codon model yield Pearson's R 2 that are competitive with, or superior to all, amino acid language models for any species.",
    "On several species, for example when predicting protein or transcript abundance in the yeasts P. pastoris and S. cerevisiae, the codon language model is substantially superior to any other models.",
    "The observation that CaLM can match or outperform amino acid language models, including those that had over 50 times",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s42256-024-00791-0 more parameters and were trained on significantly more data, further reinforces the hypothesis that codon language models are able to capture biological features of the sequences that are inaccessible to amino acid language models."
  ]
}